                        The State of Sikkim in India has been at the forefront of environmental protection, making significant strides in the realm of green"><link rel="canonical" href="https://www.taylorfrancis.com/chapters/edit/10.4324/9781003795001-2/green-ip-regime-issues-environment-protection-state-sikkim-legal-perspective-dilip-pandey"><script type="application/ld+json" id="jsonld">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Chapter","@id":"10.4324/9781003795001-2","bookFormat":"Ebook","datePublished":"","bookEdition":"1st Edition","url":"https://www.taylorfrancis.com/chapters/edit/10.4324/9781003795001-2/green-ip-regime-issues-environment-protection-state-sikkim-legal-perspective-dilip-pandey","author":{"@type":"Person","givenName":"Dilip","familyName":"Pandey"},"genre":"Environment and Sustainability, Law","name":"Green IP Regime and the Issues of Environment Protection in the State of Sikkim: A Legal Perspective","numberOfPages":13,"description":"\n                        The State of Sikkim in India has been at the forefront of environmental protection, making significant strides in the realm of green","image":"https://images.tandf.co.uk/common/jackets/crclarge/978100379/9781003795001.jpg","publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Taylor & Francis","logo":"https://taylorfrancis.com/assets/img/tfgroup-logo.svg","url":"https://taylorfrancis.com"},"publisherImprint":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Routledge","location":{"@type":"Place","address":""}},"identifier":{"@type":"PropertyValue","propertyID":"DOI","value":"10.4324/9781003795001-2"}}</script><meta property="og:url" content="https://www.taylorfrancis.com/chapters/edit/10.4324/9781003795001-2/green-ip-regime-issues-environment-protection-state-sikkim-legal-perspective-dilip-pandey"><meta property="og:type" content="books.book"><meta property="og:site_name" content="Taylor &amp; Francis"><meta property="og:description" content="
                        The State of Sikkim in India has been at the forefront of environmental protection, making significant strides in the realm of green"><meta property="og:image" content="http://images.tandf.co.uk/common/jackets/crclarge/978100379/9781003795001.jpg"><meta property="og:image:secure_url" content="https://images.tandf.co.uk/common/jackets/crclarge/978100379/9781003795001.jpg"><meta property="og:image:alt" content="Green IP Regime and the Issues of Environment Protection in the State of Sikkim: A Legal Perspective"><meta name="audience" content="all"><meta name="distribution" content="global"><meta name="citation_title" content="Green IP Regime and the Issues of Environment Protection in the State of Sikkim: A Legal Perspective"><meta name="citation_publisher" content="Routledge"><meta name="citation_pdf_url" content="https://api.taylorfrancis.com/content/chapters/edit/download?identifierName=doi&amp;identifierValue=10.4324/9781003795001-2&amp;type=chapterpdf"><meta name="citation_doi" content="10.4324/9781003795001-2"><meta name="citation_abstract" content="
                        The State of Sikkim in India has been at the forefront of environmental protection, making significant strides in the realm of green intellectual property (IP). This article examines Sikkim’s green IP regime and its implications for environmental protection. Beginning with an overview of India’s green IP regime, the article delves into specific initiatives that can be implemented in Sikkim. These include setting up a green IP cell, formulating a green IP policy, and offering financial incentives for green innovation. Challenges to environmental protection in Sikkim, such as climate change, deforestation, and pollution, are also discussed. The article argues that green IP can play a vital role in addressing these challenges by legally safeguarding green innovations and encouraging the adoption of green technologies. The article concludes by advocating for continued investment in green IP in Sikkim, emphasizing the need to create a favorable environment for green innovation. This article contributes to existing literature on green IP by providing a comprehensive overview of Sikkim’s green IP regime, discussing its potential in addressing environmental challenges, and offering recommendations for the future. The article’s relevance extends to various audiences, including policymakers, businesses, and environmental activists. Policymakers can use it to understand Sikkim’s green IP regime and explore replicating similar initiatives in other parts of India. Businesses can gain insights into the opportunities and challenges of green innovation in India. Environmental activists can leverage the article to advocate for environmental protection in Sikkim and promote the adoption of green technologies. It’s important to note that this study’s scope is limited to the legal framework for green IP in Sikkim. It does not address the economic or social impacts of green IP in the region, nor does it cover all challenges to the green IP regime in Sikkim.
                     "><meta property="citation_author" content="Dilip Pandey"><meta name="citation_xml_url" content="https://api.taylorfrancis.com/content/chapters/edit/download?identifierName=doi&amp;identifierValue=10.4324/9781003795001-2&amp;type=chapterxml"><meta name="citation_author_institution" content="Associate Professor -in Law/Dean of the Students Affair, Sikkim Government Law College, Gangtok, Lower Burtuk below Helipad,"><meta name="citation_inbook_title" content="Greening Intellectual Property for the Protection of Environment"><meta name="citation_firstpage" content="3"><meta name="citation_lastpage" content="15"></head>

